      <subsection name="Examples" id="TypeBodyPadding_Examples">
        <p id="Example1-config">
          To configure the check:
        </p>
        <div class="wrapper"><pre class="prettyprint"><code class="language-xml">
&lt;module name="Checker"&gt;
  &lt;module name="TreeWalker"&gt;
    &lt;module name="TypeBodyPadding"/&gt;
  &lt;/module&gt;
&lt;/module&gt;
</code></pre></div>
        <p id="Example1-code">
          Example:
        </p>
        <div class="wrapper"><pre class="prettyprint"><code class="language-java">
class Example1 { // violation 'Blank line required after the opening brace of type definition.'
  int x;
} // violation 'Blank line required before the closing brace of type definition.'
</code></pre></div><hr class="example-separator"/>
        <p id="Example2-config">
          To configure the check to not require blank lines for empty type bodies:
        </p>
        <div class="wrapper"><pre class="prettyprint"><code class="language-xml">
&lt;module name="Checker"&gt;
  &lt;module name="TreeWalker"&gt;
    &lt;module name="TypeBodyPadding"/&gt;
  &lt;/module&gt;
&lt;/module&gt;
</code></pre></div>
        <p id="Example2-code">
          Example:
        </p>
        <div class="wrapper"><pre class="prettyprint"><code class="language-java">
class Example2 {

  int x;

}
</code></pre></div><hr class="example-separator"/>

        <p id="Example3-config">
          To configure the check to require blank lines even for empty type bodies:
        </p>
        <div class="wrapper"><pre class="prettyprint"><code class="language-xml">
&lt;module name="Checker"&gt;
  &lt;module name="TreeWalker"&gt;
    &lt;module name="TypeBodyPadding"&gt;
      &lt;property name="allowEmpty" value="false"/&gt;
    &lt;/module&gt;
  &lt;/module&gt;
&lt;/module&gt;
</code></pre></div>
        <p id="Example3-code">
          Example:
        </p>
        <div class="wrapper"><pre class="prettyprint"><code class="language-java">
class Example3 { // violation 'Blank line required after the opening brace of type definition.'
} // violation 'Blank line required before the closing brace of type definition.'

interface Example3Int {

}
</code></pre></div><hr class="example-separator"/>

        <p id="Example4-config">
          To configure the check to not require a blank line after the starting brace:
        </p>
        <div class="wrapper"><pre class="prettyprint"><code class="language-xml">
&lt;module name="Checker"&gt;
  &lt;module name="TreeWalker"&gt;
    &lt;module name="TypeBodyPadding"&gt;
      &lt;property name="starting" value="false"/&gt;
    &lt;/module&gt;
  &lt;/module&gt;
&lt;/module&gt;
</code></pre></div>
        <p id="Example4-code">
          Example:
        </p>
        <div class="wrapper"><pre class="prettyprint"><code class="language-java">
class Example4 {
  int x;
} // violation 'Blank line required before the closing brace of type definition.'

class Example4b {

  int x;

}
</code></pre></div><hr class="example-separator"/>

        <p id="Example5-config">
          To configure the check to not require a blank line before the ending brace:
        </p>
        <div class="wrapper"><pre class="prettyprint"><code class="language-xml">
&lt;module name="Checker"&gt;
  &lt;module name="TreeWalker"&gt;
    &lt;module name="TypeBodyPadding"&gt;
      &lt;property name="ending" value="false"/&gt;
    &lt;/module&gt;
  &lt;/module&gt;
&lt;/module&gt;
</code></pre></div>
        <p id="Example5-code">
          Example:
        </p>
        <div class="wrapper"><pre class="prettyprint"><code class="language-java">
class Example5 { // violation 'Blank line required after the opening brace of type definition.'
  int x;
}

class Example5b {

  int x;
}
</code></pre></div><hr class="example-separator"/>

        <p id="Example6-config">
          To configure the check to require blank lines for inner classes too:
        </p>
        <div class="wrapper"><pre class="prettyprint"><code class="language-xml">
&lt;module name="Checker"&gt;
  &lt;module name="TreeWalker"&gt;
    &lt;module name="TypeBodyPadding"&gt;
      &lt;property name="skipInner" value="false"/&gt;
    &lt;/module&gt;
  &lt;/module&gt;
&lt;/module&gt;
</code></pre></div>
        <p id="Example6-code">
          Example:
        </p>
        <div class="wrapper"><pre class="prettyprint"><code class="language-java">
class Example6 {

  class Inner { // violation 'Blank line required after the opening brace of type definition.'
    int y;
  } // violation 'Blank line required before the closing brace of type definition.'

}
</code></pre></div><hr class="example-separator"/>

        <p id="Example7-config">
          To configure the check to require blank lines for local classes too:
        </p>
        <div class="wrapper"><pre class="prettyprint"><code class="language-xml">
&lt;module name="Checker"&gt;
  &lt;module name="TreeWalker"&gt;
    &lt;module name="TypeBodyPadding"&gt;
      &lt;property name="skipLocal" value="false"/&gt;
    &lt;/module&gt;
  &lt;/module&gt;
&lt;/module&gt;
</code></pre></div>
        <p id="Example7-code">
          Example:
        </p>
        <div class="wrapper"><pre class="prettyprint"><code class="language-java">
class Example7 {

  void method() {
    class Local { // violation 'Blank line required after the opening brace of type definition.'
      int y;
    } // violation 'Blank line required before the closing brace of type definition.'
  }

}
</code></pre></div><hr class="example-separator"/>

        <p id="Example8-config">
          To configure the check to only run on interfaces, enums,
          annotations, and records (bypassing classes):
        </p>
        <div class="wrapper"><pre class="prettyprint"><code class="language-xml">
&lt;module name="Checker"&gt;
  &lt;module name="TreeWalker"&gt;
    &lt;module name="TypeBodyPadding"&gt;
      &lt;property name="tokens" value="INTERFACE_DEF, RECORD_DEF, ENUM_DEF, ANNOTATION_DEF"/&gt;
    &lt;/module&gt;
  &lt;/module&gt;
&lt;/module&gt;
</code></pre></div>
        <p id="Example8-code">
          Example:
        </p>
        <div class="wrapper"><pre class="prettyprint"><code class="language-java">
class Example8 {
  int x;
}

interface Example8b { // violation 'Blank line required after the opening brace of type definition.'
  int x;
} // violation 'Blank line required before the closing brace of type definition.'
</code></pre></div>
      </subsection>

